We will further add, that even in such a ease, the ally is not bound, if there be no hope of a good result. For such alliances are contracted, not for the sake of evil results, but of good. An ally however is to be defended even against another confederate, except there be some special stipulation to the contrary in some previous convention. Thus the Coreyreans, if their cause was good, might have received defensive aid from the Athenians, even against the Corinthiam, who were their old allies.

V.
